  "body": "### Description\n\nThe Vert.x `EventBus` as described by the [Quarkus guide](https://quarkus.io/guides/reactive-event-bus) looks like a powerful alternative to asynchronous CDI events and other alternatives. Unfortunately it doesn't support context propagation. Thus, for example, the OpenTelemetry tracing context is \"lost\" when sending an event over the `EventBus`.\r\n\r\nIf this works as designed and context propagation cannot be added, I think this should explicitly be stated in the Quarkus guide.\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\n_No response_",
